Velenkosini Hlabisa has been elected as the new president of the Inkatha Freedom Party. ULUNDI - Velenkosini Hlabisa has been elected as the new leader of the Inkatha Freedom Party. The party's hosting its national elective conference in uLundi in KwaZulu-Natal. Outgoing IFP leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi said he's proud of his legacy. Hlabisa has been groomed to take over from Buthelezi, who was at the helm for four decades. READ: End of an era as Buthelezi steps down It seems unlikely that Hlabisa will take the IFP in a different direction. He shares the same vision and approach towards the Zulu King as Buthelezi.